      "summary": "founded in 2004, OBAT Helpers Inc. is a dedicated humanitarian organization focused on <cite id=\"1\">breaking the cycle of poverty</cite> for displaced and marginalized communities in Bangladesh. The organization operates with a high degree of transparency, evidenced by its <cite id=\"2\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite> and an <cite id=\"3\">overall score of 90.90.33333333333333/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. OBAT's mission is executed through a multi-sectoral approach that includes <cite id=\"4\">education support, healthcare services, and economic empowerment</cite>. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"5\">total revenue of $2,184,558</cite>, primarily driven by <cite id=\"6\">$1,992,930 in public contributions</cite>. A key differentiator for OBAT is its operational efficiency; it maintains a <cite id=\"7\">fundraising efficiency of $0.06 per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that the vast majority of donor funds are directed toward its <cite id=\"8\">50 educational projects and 3 health clinics</cite>. As a <cite id=\"9\">zakat-eligible entity</cite>, OBAT provides a critical pathway for Muslim donors to support the <cite id=\"10\">fuqara (poor) and masakin (needy)</cite> within the Rohingya refugee camps and other internally displaced person (IDP) settlements. The organization's impact is quantified by a <cite id=\"11\">cost per beneficiary of approximately $100.01</cite>, which is considered exceptional for its advocacy and direct-service delivery model.",
